conform /kənˈfɔːm/

(conforming,conformed,conforms) 

1. V-I If something conforms to something such as a law or someone's wishes, it is of the required type or quality. (与法律、愿望等) 相符合 

例： The lamp has been designed to conform to new safety standards. 该灯设计得符合新的安全标准。 

2. V-I If you conform , you behave in the way that you are expected or supposed to behave. 守规矩 

例： Many children who can't or don't conform are bullied. 许多不守规矩的孩子受欺负。

